<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–2848: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ward</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-28T10:00:00+09:00">July 28,
                                    1948—10 a. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 28—3:47 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>318. My telegram 316 yesterday. Students continued parade through city
                            until 1630 hours, without serious incident and with no anti-foreign
                            expression. Marchers orderly but evidenced genuine feeling. Police
                            vicinity demonstrators did not bear arms.</p>
                        <p>All non-military rail traffic Mukden area halted yesterday morning by
                            strike, workers demanded food allowance equal that railway workers in
                            intramural China and immediate payment wages in arrears, No violence.
                            Demands accepted early today and traffic resumed.</p>
                        <p>Sent Nanking 399; repeated Department 318.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>